</tr></tbody></table>
<p><i><b>Blindsight</b></i> is a <a href="/wiki/Hard_science_fiction" title="Hard science fiction">hard science fiction</a> novel by Canadian writer <a href="/wiki/Peter_Watts_(author)" title="Peter Watts (author)">Peter Watts</a>, published by <a href="/wiki/Tor_Books" title="Tor Books">Tor Books</a> in 2006. It won the <a href="/wiki/Seiun_Award" title="Seiun Award">Seiun Award</a> for best translated novel,<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> and was nominated for the <a href="/wiki/Hugo_Award_for_Best_Novel" title="Hugo Award for Best Novel">Hugo Award for Best Novel</a>,<sup id="cite_ref-url_Hugo_Nominees_(press_release)_3-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-url_Hugo_Nominees_(press_release)-3">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> the <a href="/wiki/John_W._Campbell_Memorial_Award_for_Best_Science_Fiction_Novel" title="John W. Campbell Memorial Award for Best Science Fiction Novel">John W. Campbell Memorial Award for Best Science Fiction Novel</a>,<sup id="cite_ref-WWE-Campbell_4-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-WWE-Campbell-4">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> and the <a href="/wiki/Locus_Award_for_Best_Science_Fiction_Novel" title="Locus Award for Best Science Fiction Novel">Locus Award for Best Science Fiction Novel</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-WWE-LocusSF_5-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-WWE-LocusSF-5">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> The novel follows a crew of astronauts sent out as the third wave, following two series of probes, to investigate a <a href="/wiki/Trans-Neptunian" class="mw-redirect" title="Trans-Neptunian">trans-Neptunian</a> Kuiper belt comet dubbed "Burns-Caulfield" that has been found to be transmitting an unidentified radio signal to an as-yet unknown destination elsewhere in the Solar System, followed by their subsequent <a href="/wiki/First_contact_(science_fiction)" title="First contact (science fiction)">first contact</a>. The novel explores themes of <a href="/wiki/Identity_(philosophy)" title="Identity (philosophy)">identity</a>, <a href="/wiki/Consciousness" title="Consciousness">consciousness</a>, <a href="/wiki/Free_will" title="Free will">free will</a>, <a href="/wiki/Artificial_intelligence" title="Artificial intelligence">artificial intelligence</a>, <a href="/wiki/Neurology" title="Neurology">neurology</a> and <a href="/wiki/Game_theory" title="Game theory">game theory</a> as well as <a href="/wiki/Evolution" title="Evolution">evolution</a> and <a href="/wiki/Biology" title="Biology">biology</a>.
</p><p><i>Blindsight</i> is available online under a <a href="/wiki/Creative_Commons_license" title="Creative Commons license">Creative Commons license</a>. Its sequel (or “<a href="/wiki/Sidequel" class="mw-redirect" title="Sidequel">sidequel</a>”) <i><a href="/wiki/Echopraxia_(novel)" title="Echopraxia (novel)">Echopraxia</a></i> came out in 2014.
</p>
